pages.title: How To Dispose Of Sulfuric Acid And Clean Up Spills
pages.description: Learn How To Safely Dispose Of Sulfuric Acid Waste Dilute and neutralize H2SO4 to clean up spills in homes and labs. Read about the proper way to dispose of sulfuric acid, here. Find out how to clean up sulfuric acid spills, here. Recommended procedures for chemical disposal are listed, here. To neutralize sulfuric acid, pour it into a solution of sodium hydroxide. Use sodium bicarbonate (or baking soda) to neutralize battery acid (sulfuric acid).      Learn how to clean up sulfuric acid spills, here. Dispose of the spent sulfuric acid and disposables contaminated with sulfuric acid as hazardous waste.  Sulfuric acid can be disposed of by being placed in sealed containers and by being absorbed in vermiculite, dry sand, or earth. ...

items.title: Sulfuric Acid 96% Solution, Semiconductor/Electronic Grade
items.description: Sulfuric Acid, also known as Mattling Acid, is a mineral acid that is recognized as Oil of Vitriol. It is highly acidic and corrosive due to its low pH. It must be handled carefully and kept away from incompatible materials such as water, organic compounds, metals, amines, bases, and high temperatures.
